Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AlgebraProblemGenerator
    The class mmodels the design for an algebra problem.
    Audio
    This class is responsible for playing all the audio files found in the game.
    Boss
    This data class models the Boss and is a type of entity.
    BossLevel
    The class is responsible for creating a boss level, which is a type of Level.
    Button
    This data class models a button, and is a type of entity.
    CreditRoll
    The class creates a credit animation crediting those who created the graphics and other resources for the game.
    DirectionHelper
    A simple class that defines integer constants used as direction variables in other classes.
    Entity
    This data class models a generic entity, which other classes will be extending.
    FractionProblemGenerator
    The class mmodels the design for a fraction problem.
    HighScoreEntry
    This data class models an entry in the high score table.
    HighScoreList
    This class contians the list of high score entries and is responsible for modifying it as well as reading and writing to the high score test file.
    Introduction
    The class creates an animation used to represent and introduce the story to the user.
    Level
    The class is responsible for creating a generic level.
    LevelReader
    This class is responsible for reading a level file and returning a 2D array of rooms that is than read by the MazeLevel class.
    MainMenu
    This class is responsible for creating the main menu panel, which contains many buttons navigating to different parts of the program.
    MazeLevel
    The class responsible for creating a basic maze level (subtype of Level), which includes a maze.
    MultiplicationProblemGenerator
    The class models the design for a multiplication problem.
    NumericalLabyrinthApp
    Creates in instance of the NumericalLabyrinthFrame class, which runs the entire game.
    NumericalLabyrinthFrame
    Creates an instances of each level, boss, and the menu, and adds each one to the frame.
    Player
    This class models a player object and extends Entity.
    Problem
    This data class models a math problem.
    ProblemGenerator
    The class models the design for an abstract problem.
    Room
    The class mmodels the design for a room.
    SplashScreen
    Creates an small window that displays the company logo, then disappears after a few seconds.
    Timer
    Models a stopwatch thread running concurrently alongside other aspects of the program.
